1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:02,240
Do not bring your issues
with Mercan into this.

2
00:00:02,520 --> 00:00:03,959
I mean because of the movie night.

3
00:00:03,960 --> 00:00:05,016
So there is no misunderstanding.

4
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:06,040
What happened...

5
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:08,040
I was going to talk to you about that.

6
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:09,920
We said ten o’clock.

7
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:13,960
Aslı, everything is going as planned.

8
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:16,360
Is Ateş there?

9
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:18,600
No, he went to Cemal.

10
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:20,400
Ok.

11
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:24,000
I will hang up. Handle
it before Ateş arrives.

12
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:26,280
Do not worry, I will.

13
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:30,120
I arranged a last-minute meeting
with an important investor.

14
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:32,280
We will have dinner tonight.

15
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:34,280
The topics fall right into your field.

16
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:38,120
Would you come to the dinner with me?

17
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:40,360
Mercan is not at the company.

18
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,160
I saw her entering a restaurant.

19
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:43,520
Which restaurant?

20
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:48,920
I'm sure she'll love it.

21
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:57,320
Could I... // try this on you?

22
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:59,240
To see how it looks.

23
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:05,480
If it puts your mind at ease, try it.

24
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:20,240
Are you okay?

25
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:21,680
What happened here?

26
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,360
Get out of here.

27
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,880
This is my favorite movie.

28
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:38,360
We will not get a dime out
of Mr. Ateş after this point.

29
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:39,400
Mercan will not even look me in the eye.

30
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:40,840
I came out of this the worst off.

31
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,440
You know how partnerships work.

32
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,760
When we win, we both win.

33
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,880
When we lose, we both lose.

34
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,960
Then you will throw the rats on that
boat overboard and pay me my money.

35
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:53,560
If you do not pay, I will
tell Mercan everything.

36
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,880
You make me say too many if onlys.

37
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:00,080
Did you say "if only" after you
promised me and gone to dinner with Nezir?

38
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:03,640
Or for that bracelet
you accepted as a gift.

39
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,760
Why are you being so possessive?

40
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,880
I do not understand this much
anger over a fake marriage.

41
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,360
Because.

42
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,600
Did that stone heart soften?

43
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:19,520
Or is something else happening
in the heart we thought was stone?

44
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:24,400
You... you are not jealous of me, are you?

45
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,160
What nonsense are you talking about?

46
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,639
Whenever you see me with Nezir,

47
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:33,600
you always assume the worst.

48
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,400
You react far too harshly.

49
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:39,080
When Nezir is involved, you
don’t even hear yourself.

50
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,840
You did the same thing
last time, about the flowers.

51
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:45,280
You used words that crossed the line.

52
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,840
So naturally, I thought you were jealous.

53
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,840
You can’t be jealous of me, right?

54
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:08,680
What are you accusing me of?

55
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,400
What is there between you and this man?

56
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:20,080
Don’t. Stop right there.

57
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:22,280
Don’t cross my line.

58
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,640
You don’t get to say a
single word about my honor.

59
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:34,720
Who do you think you are? Who are you? Who?

60
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:37,200
How dare you talk to me like that?

61
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,936
No one gets to talk to me like this.

62
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:39,960
I do.

63
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,920
I do.

64
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,000
Then don’t mess around with other men.

65
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,320
Who do you think you are?

66
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,280
Or is that what you want?

67
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,120
I don’t know how you got that idea,

68
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:10,320
but get this pointless
thought out of your head.

69
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,920
Fine.

70
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,320
I will.

71
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,440
I wasn’t giving it much of a chance anyway.

72
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,960
Jealousy is a human feeling.

73
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:25,880
Expecting that from someone as cold
as you would be ridiculous, I guess.

74
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,920
I did not think anything like that anyway.

75
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:38,080
Then why am I being
subjected to these tantrums?

76
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:44,920
No matter what, even if only
for 187 days, you are my wife.

77
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,480
You carry my last name.

78
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,480
That is all there is to it.

79
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,480
Get these unnecessary
thoughts out of your head.

80
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:58,920
I am saying it again.

81
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,279
It is a last name matter.

82
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,480
It is always you are my wife.

83
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:03,960
Aren’t you?

84
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,600
I remember.

85
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,599
You do not need to remind me all the time.

86
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,840
Good.

87
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,680
It is good that you remember.

88
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:15,280
Draw a line between you and Nezir.

89
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:20,400
As long as you do not forget
the last name, there is no problem.

90
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,760
Setting limits for me is not your job.

91
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,280
All my life...

92
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:32,560
As Mercan Yıldırım, I decide
myself who I draw boundaries with.

93
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,600
You are a Karahan.

94
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,280
You are carrying my last name.

95
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,480
You will draw your boundaries accordingly.

96
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,600
Nezir did not buy me any gift or anything.

97
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,800
Even if he had, I would
not have accepted it.

98
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:20,440
If you knew me even a little, you
would know I would not accept it anyway.

99
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,760
He bought the bracelet for Demet.

100
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,600
He was only asking my opinion.

101
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:38,400
I do not know whether you would
feel ashamed of what you are saying.

102
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,360
This is the truth.

103
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,760
Setting limits for me is not your job.

104
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,520
All my life...

105
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:06,400
As Mercan Yıldırım, I decide
myself who I draw boundaries with.

106
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,256
So tell me, what did you do at the concert?

107
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,280
How was it, tell me?

108
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:24,520
If my brother asks, could you please say

109
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,680
that we all went to the concert
together as a company, Yaşar?

110
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,119
Do not worry, I have got it.

111
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,800
You are amazing.

112
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,440
I am very good at lying, no one notices.

113
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,920
They do, they do.

114
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,360
And it is noticed very clearly.

115
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:42,400
Ms. Demet, please do not do
business with lies and tricks.

116
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,840
Especially do not do
it by trusting Mr. Yaşar.

117
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:51,040
Also, I would be very happy if you did not
mix your private life with your work life.

118
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,200
Good luck to you, Ms. Zahide.

119
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,920
Thank you, Ms. Demet.

120
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,480
Did you want something, Ms. Zahide?

121
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:04,440
I wanted the monthly reports, Mr. Yaşar.

122
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,480
Are they ready?

123
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,640
No, I have not finished them yet.

124
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,856
But they will be on your
desk by tomorrow morning.

125
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:11,880
Today.

126
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,080
It would be very good if they are
on my desk by the end of the workday.

127
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:18,840
Ms. Zahide, should you
socialize a little as well?

128
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,736
Whatever you do, life
is not only about work.

129
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:23,296
If you went to a party or a concert
or something, to clear your head?

130
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,080
Look at how people go out and have fun.

131
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,799
Mr. Yaşar.

132
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:29,480
Someone has to work too, you know.

133
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,720
There was a story, remember.

134
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,680
The grasshopper and the ant.

135
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,240
Do you know that story?

136
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,800
That is exactly it.

137
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:40,840
Oh Ms. Zahide, do not
give me ant praise now.

138
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:44,560
As if the ant did any good by leaving
the grasshopper at the door in the cold.

139
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,440
So there is nothing to be proud of in that.

140
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:47,760
If there were, I would know.

141
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,800
There is not, right?

142
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,400
You would know very well.

143
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,960
Looks like they have not made up yet.

144
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,080
I think so too.

145
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,360
You cannot even gossip
properly with a woman, brother.

146
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:28,640
An antisocial woman.

147
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,320
What will happen?

148
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,960
Antisocial.

149
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,600
Hello.

150
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,040
Did it work?

151
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:41,920
Great.

152
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,400
I am on my way.

153
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,320
Come on, Cemal.

154
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:16,920
Has it not passed yet?

155
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:18,960
It will pass.

156
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,200
Do not make any insinuations, Cemal.

157
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:33,960
Even if you do not speak, I
understand what you are trying to say.

158
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,040
You do, true.

159
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,640
But I know you too.

160
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:41,319
So that means even if
you do not spell it out,

161
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:43,600
I understand what is on your mind as well.

162
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:46,360
You have fallen into a war.

163
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:48,920
And it is clearly a big one.

164
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:53,160
On one side, your feelings,
on the other, your reason.

165
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,840
Which one will win, I
honestly have no idea.

166
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:58,880
But there is one thing I know.

167
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,400
You hate losing.

168
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:06,920
The strange part is, no matter
what, you will be the one who loses.

169
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,680
So what I am saying is, maybe
you should walk away from this war.

170
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:20,320
I do not have that right, Cemal.

171
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,280
I will not forget why I came here.

172
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:28,680
I cannot forget.

173
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,040
Nothing will make me forget.

174
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,280
I will rip out anything
that stands in the way.

175
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,680
You will rip it out, fair enough.

176
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:44,480
But the heart you are
pretending does not exist.

177
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,280
How will you keep that under control?

178
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:51,080
Then I will rip that heart out too.

179
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:56,360
Besides, it is not what you think.

180
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,160
I only wanted to make her happy.

181
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,480
So be it, excuse me.

182
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,520
Am I jealous?

183
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,720
No.

184
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:22,560
No, impossible.

185
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:51,080
Come on now.

186
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,480
What else?

187
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:58,280
Son, what business did you
have being out with Zehra?

188
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:01,200
And there you are, sitting face to
face, drinking tea in a tea garden.

189
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,136
Berat, look me in the
eye and tell me the truth.

190
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,216
Is there something going on between you?

191
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:06,040
Mom, it is not like that, no.

192
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:09,240
I mean, we ran into
each other by the seaside.

193
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:11,240
Then we said let us
have a tea, that is all.

194
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:16,160
That is it. We already work in
the same place. We are together 24 7.

195
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,376
You are blowing this way out of proportion.

196
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,040
Honestly, your interrogations never end.

197
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:21,800
Listen to me, Berat.

198
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,960
Son, that girl is not a reliable girl.

199
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,760
Her eyes spell trouble.

200
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:27,720
I am warning you, son, do not you dare.

201
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:31,120
You make one mistake and you
will suffer for it your whole life.

202
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,480
You will not see that girl again.

203
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,560
Do you understand me?

204
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:35,680
Hi.

205
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,920
Where have you been all day?

206
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,240
I stopped by the bank.

207
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,480
The line was long.

208
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,640
You stopped by the bank.

209
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,120
You had so much money in the bank.

210
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:47,920
Insallah.

211
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:52,440
What have I been dealing
with because of you people?

212
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,360
Your troubles never end.

213
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,480
Your worries never end.

214
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,400
Your incidents never end.

215
00:14:58,440 --> 00:14:59,520
Are you going to kill me?

216
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,720
Inshallah, mom.

217
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,040
No, I get it now.

218
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,040
Allah Allah...

219
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,400
You are going to kill me.

220
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,600
I get it.

221
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,400
What happened, brother?

222
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:12,960
How would I know?

223
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,840
She is shouting, that is all.

224
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,880
It is my fault.

225
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,640
I got carried away by stupid
thoughts and even hinted at them to her.

226
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,440
Who am I, and jealousy?

227
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:29,280
Heartless.

228
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,480
Heartless thing.

229
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,520
Ms. Mercan.

230
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,280
Come in, Yaşar.

231
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:41,600
Well...

232
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:42,640
What happened?

233
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:49,040
They fixed your phone, but unfortunately
they could not recover the messages.

234
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:50,760
That is really bad.

235
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,320
Anyway, nothing to be done.

236
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,320
Thanks anyway.

237
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:58,720
You are welcome.

238
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,000
Ms. Mercan?

239
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:04,720
If there is anything else I can do?

240
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,240
No, no, Yaşar.

241
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,480
Thank you.

242
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,240
Alright, Ms. Mercan.

243
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,400
Good luck. Thanks.

244
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:18,320
Come on now...

245
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:23,960
What is it?

246
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,520
You look down again.

247
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,200
I wonder why.

248
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,120
Same old Ateş Karahan headaches.

249
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,560
Still not sorted it out?

250
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:39,080
We are tied in knots.

251
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,640
Hard.

252
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:42,120
Untangable.

253
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,440
The messages are gone.

254
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,000
I am sorry.

255
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:50,840
Anyway.

256
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,920
No point in souring our mood over it now.

257
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,680
Listen, I was going to say.

258
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:58,280
Why do not you come over
tonight, we will talk a bit.

259
00:16:58,920 --> 00:16:59,920
Ah, Inshallah.

260
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,599
It would have been great, but.

261
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,800
If I had not already promised.

262
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:09,160
I am going to a concert with Burak tonight.

263
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:16,680
So that is the reason for
the sparkle in your eyes, huh?

264
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,080
Come on.

265
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,240
My brother does not know.

266
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,680
I have been so buried in my own troubles.

267
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,480
I did not even notice your excitement.

268
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:26,960
Forgive me, please.

269
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,480
Do not be silly.

270
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,576
You have been fighting
for your life for months.

271
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,320
Am I something you need to worry about too?

272
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,080
We used to talk about everything.

273
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:40,400
Now we cannot even
share the simplest things.

274
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,760
Do not schedule any meetings
for a few days, Zahide.

275
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:49,680
Postpone the existing ones too, please.

276
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:51,640
And can you leave the
project files on my desk?

277
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,200
Of course, I will take care
of it right away, Mr. Ateş.

278
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,960
While I was trying to make you happy...

279
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,120
how did you end up going next to his name?

280
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:32,600
If only you had believed me just once.

281
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,000
Always by your side...

282
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,040
In the end, I will be the
one left holding the bag.

283
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,560
You cannot be jealous of me, can you?

284
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,760
Ateş... I have a small
thing to take care of.

285
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,360
Let me finish it and then we can go.

286
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:32,680
Alright.

287
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,280
Are you okay?

288
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:36,040
I am fine, nothing wrong.

289
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:06,880
So you are here.

290
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,080
I was looking for you.

291
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,400
What is it, Ms. Müzeyyen?

292
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:16,600
Did you miss me?

293
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,000
How pathetic you are.

294
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,519
Not a penny in your pocket...

295
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:30,800
and you think you can run against
me for the association presidency?

296
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,280
So you found out.

297
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,600
I gave years of my
life to that association.

298
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:45,880
Before money... the effort you
put in and your reputation matter.

299
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:51,960
You think you can show some money
and become the president in three days?

300
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:01,880
You may have money.

301
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:08,080
But you are not a people person.

302
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:13,200
The person to be elected
to the association...

303
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:17,360
should be known in society... you know...

304
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:20,960
someone with strong social ties.

305
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:24,560
Of course they will choose me over you.

306
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:31,320
I will watch your effort
with great pleasure.

307
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,600
We will see.

308
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,400
Ms. Nermin...

309
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:50,400
I found a key like this in the garden.

310
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,120
It does not fit any of the rooms.

311
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:54,600
It is not for the annex either.

312
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,680
Where in the garden did you find it?

313
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,760
Where we park the cars.

314
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:02,399
My brother cleans that area
very often actually but...

315
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,320
it looks like it was dropped recently.

316
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,880
Alright dear, alright.

317
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,800
Shall we go out to dinner together?

318
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:32,080
No.

319
00:22:32,081 --> 00:22:34,160
I am going home.

320
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,319
I would love to, brother, but...

321
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:44,880
we are going to a concert with
people from the company tonight.

322
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:39,560
You cancelled tomorrow’s meeting.

323
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,360
Yes.

324
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:53,240
Wow, the bracelet shines
beautifully, brother.

325
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:56,000
Thank you so much.

326
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:58,240
I love this gift.

327
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:12,560
Wear it in good health.

328
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,520
He bought the bracelet for Demet.

329
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,200
He was only asking my opinion.

330
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:30,760
She told the truth.

331
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,640
The bracelet was for Demet.

332
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,040
Good evening.

333
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:41,200
Your bank account is almost empty, Haydar.

334
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,520
I am not used to this at
all, I am really struggling.

335
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:49,040
And that woman Müzeyyen keeps
mocking me for being broke.

336
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:52,320
I know, Nermin, I know, be patient.

337
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,080
I will sort out the money issue.

338
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:59,360
Haydar, you are a man who
creates money out of nothing.

339
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:02,760
I have never seen you struggle
this much to make money.

340
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,240
I said I will handle it, Nermin.

341
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:07,720
Do not get on my throat,
stop coming at me like this.

342
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:11,120
Alright dear, alright.

343
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:13,040
If you say so...

344
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:16,160
I cannot deny your right either.

345
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:21,000
You have always kept me in
luxury since we got married.

346
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,040
These days will pass too, of course.

347
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:32,600
By the way, could this key be yours?

348
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,040
No.

349
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,240
Where did you find it?

350
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,720
Çiçek found it in the garden.

351
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:41,360
She tried all the room doors in
the house but it did not fit any.

352
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:45,480
Why would anyone carry a
room key on them anyway?

353
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:47,560
I do not know.

354
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,120
It is very strange.

355
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,640
What is strange about it, Nermin?

356
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:54,640
Anyone hearing you would think
you found a safe key full of money.

357
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,520
Is this what you are stuck on now?

358
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,200
Here.

359
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:25,799
Brother, please, this is
not right. Look, brother...

360
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:30,280
Çiçek, you have been yapping
and grinding my brain all day.

361
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:32,160
Just stop.

362
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:33,680
I am talking for your own good.

363
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:35,360
I am not interfering in your life, look.

364
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:37,200
Brother, what harm have you seen from her?

365
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:38,760
What did this girl do to you?

366
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:43,800
At heart, she is a good girl.

367
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,560
Brother. What?

368
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:50,240
Since she came to the mansion, she
has not left a single thing undone to us.

369
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:51,280
Admit it.

370
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,800
Zehra bossed us around
more than Ms. Müzeyyen.

371
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:59,999
She did what that witch Müzeyyen said.

372
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,160
She carried out her orders.

373
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:04,720
Brother, my dear brother, look...

374
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,320
She is not someone for you.

375
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:11,200
Çiçek, there is nothing there, sweetheart.

376
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:13,160
We just had a tea, that is all.

377
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:14,880
For God’s sake.

378
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,400
Cemal.

379
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:35,120
Would you mind sitting up front?

380
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:40,880
I do not want to sit in the front.

381
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,440
Alright, as you wish.

382
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:45,600
Works for me.

383
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,960
That makes sense.

384
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:51,000
I think so too.

385
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:53,600
One needs a bit of peace.

386
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:56,720
Yes, peace is important of course.

387
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,560
Alright then.

388
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:00,720
Yes, alright then.

389
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,440
Weren’t you going with Nezir?

390
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:07,960
Why would I go with Nezir?

391
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:11,480
If you are going to talk nonsense
like this, you can take a taxi.

392
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:35,040
Who do you think you are?

393
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,720
Do you think you have
the right to kick me out?

394
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:41,080
Out of this car, no less?

395
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:46,521
This is you setting boundaries,
and it has been going on all morning.

396
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:47,920
Patience.

397
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:50,120
Yes, it is my right.

398
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:51,480
Everything is my right.

399
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:52,800
Do you have any objection? I do.

400
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,760
It got really cold.

401
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,440
Should we turn on the AC or something?

402
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,920
She only arrived yesterday.

403
00:29:59,800 --> 00:30:00,800
Aslı, enough.

404
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:07,040
My head has been buzzing enough today.

405
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,560
Mine too.

406
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:13,120
A bit of peace, a bit of silence.

407
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,000
I agree.

408
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:21,360
No, not this one.

409
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:47,080
I checked all the doors.

410
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:49,880
This is the only one left.

411
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,360
Finally.

412
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,200
What are you doing here?

413
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,560
Nothing, what would I be doing?

414
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:12,120
Çiçek found the key in the garden.

415
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:15,640
I tried all the doors but it did not open.

416
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:18,200
I was just trying to figure
out where it belongs to.

417
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:39,640
Oh Ateş, oh.

418
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,520
Good grief.

419
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:06,120
I am exhausted, completely exhausted.

420
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:10,600
Mom, look.

421
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,480
I finished the scarf.

422
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:19,920
How does it look?

423
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:23,680
It looks nice.

424
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:24,840
Wasn’t it blue?

425
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:27,520
No, this one.

426
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,400
Did you forget, mom?

427
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:36,720
It looks great, a brown scarf.

428
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:38,520
Does it look good?

429
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:40,880
It does.

430
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:52,840
Çiçek.

431
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:59,520
This thing about the loan shark debt
Malik paid is really bothering me, my girl.

432
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:03,360
Isn’t this boy a salaried
employee in this mansion?

433
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:04,760
Like us.

434
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,080
Isn’t he a driver?

435
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,240
So where did he find all that money?

436
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:09,800
What did he do?

437
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:12,056
Did he not eat or drink and
save everything he earned?

438
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,080
Did he keep it all?

439
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:17,880
I mean mom, nobody does
this for someone else.

440
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:23,400
So he must really love us.

441
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,320
But my girl, we do not know this boy.

442
00:34:26,720 --> 00:34:29,840
He never properly talked
about his mother or his father.

443
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:30,680
We know nothing.

444
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,760
It is like he came out of a tree hollow.

445
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:34,960
True.

446
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:36,840
He never mentioned them.

447
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:43,920
Anyway, let us not wrong the boy.

448
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:45,680
After all, he paid our debt.

449
00:34:50,240 --> 00:34:51,240
Where is your brother?

450
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,360
I did not see him, mom.

451
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:01,120
Girl, I hope he did not go
wandering around with Zehra again.

452
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:03,320
Oh no mom, do not worry.

453
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:05,880
I talked to my brother.

454
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:07,800
He said there is nothing between them.

455
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:11,800
Rest easy.

456
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,960
God forbid, heaven and earth protect us.

457
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:18,720
A daughter in law like
Zehra, keep her far from homes.

458
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:19,920
Far from homes.

459
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:21,360
On the enemy’s head.

460
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:22,840
God forbid.

461
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:31,600
Since you are curious what kind
of daughter in law I would be.

462
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:33,280
Wait and see.

463
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,400
Do not think I will
forget what you said to me.

464
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:06,280
You have gone too far now.

465
00:36:17,680 --> 00:36:19,360
Dear, shall we talk?

466
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,040
Weren’t they on bad terms?

467
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:38,520
They were not talking because
he had you kidnapped, remember?

468
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:42,680
I am absolutely sure this girl knows
every dirty thing her father has done.

469
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,000
They are playing both sides.

470
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,680
Like good cop, bad cop.

471
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,000
Come on, inside.

472
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:55,800
Why do you ignore what I say, Ateş?

473
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:59,400
Why do you give this
girl so many privileges?

474
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:01,640
After all, she is Haydar’s daughter.

475
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:03,920
Aslı, enough.

476
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,440
Do not drag this out any further.

477
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:10,080
When it comes to her, I am
always the one who drags things out.

478
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:11,600
Why?

479
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:14,040
If there is something
else, say it so we know.

480
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:17,000
Like what?

481
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:23,160
I will not even form a single sentence
in response to your aggressive attitude.

482
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:36,760
I think you are wrong, Aslı.

483
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,200
Do not go this hard on Ateş.

484
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:58,480
Dad, no matter what you say,
you cannot justify what you did.

485
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,440
My concern is not justifying myself.

486
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:03,240
My concern is you standing
by that man against me.

487
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:05,320
On this, I am on his side.

488
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:06,920
Because you made a mistake.

489
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:08,520
A very big mistake.

490
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:10,120
To me, it is not a mistake at all.

491
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:12,480
I wanted to teach him a lesson.

492
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,696
The man took over everything
I had, took it from me.

493
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:15,720
He never gets enough.

494
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,800
He talks about 187 days, all nonsense.

495
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:20,040
He is stalling us, my girl.

496
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:22,880
That man has other plans, do you not see?

497
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:25,920
Even so, it does not justify what you did.

498
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:30,360
Look, Ateş wants to destroy me.

499
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,480
I will not allow that.

500
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:36,240
You will stand by me as
my daughter, that is all.

501
00:38:50,480 --> 00:38:52,720
The mansion has been quiet for a few days.

502
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,520
Our days have passed without incident.

503
00:38:56,160 --> 00:39:00,240
Honestly, the only thing that matters
to me is being with you, my love.

504
00:39:00,560 --> 00:39:01,880
Same for me.

505
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:05,320
But so many things
happened that affected us.

506
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:07,960
Thank God everything is back to how it was.

507
00:39:08,240 --> 00:39:09,240
Thank God.

508
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:10,800
And you are right, my Çiçek.

509
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:14,439
Since we live here,
inevitably the negativity

510
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,480
affects us too, of course.

511
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,720
That is true.

512
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:21,440
Anyway.

513
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:26,520
Now that things have calmed
down, you can invite your family.

514
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,760
You have not seen them
in a long time after all.

515
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:31,680
I can finally meet them too.

516
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,480
By the way.

517
00:39:35,920 --> 00:39:37,080
What kind of people are they?

518
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,240
You never told me.

519
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:42,040
Like you and me, my love.

520
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,360
Normal people.

521
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,040
Like you and me.

522
00:39:44,041 --> 00:39:45,600
But how exactly?

523
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:47,640
I do not really know.

524
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:51,320
You will find out anyway.

525
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:54,000
Come on, tell me now.

526
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:55,480
What is your mother like?

527
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:56,440
Your father?

528
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:58,000
Who do you take after?

529
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,840
Will they like me?

530
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:03,320
They will.

531
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:04,600
Of course they will.

532
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,840
And even if they do
not, it does not matter.

533
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:11,680
What matters is our love, right my love?

534
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:15,520
Someone might see us.

535
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:20,800
That is true, but we
cannot be happy like this.

536
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:23,600
We can, my love.

537
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:24,880
Why not?

538
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:26,760
Yes?

539
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:31,400
Why did he not talk here?

540
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,520
That is strange.

541
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:35,160
Who could it be?

542
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:00,760
You got your phone back.

543
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:04,680
Yes, but the messages were deleted.

544
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:08,440
Well, look at that.

545
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:11,360
I checked myself.

546
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:18,480
Even though you heard what Demet
said, what are you still saying?

547
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:21,280
There is still no message at all.

548
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:24,240
I am talking about the bracelet.

549
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:25,920
You do not even apologize.

550
00:41:27,240 --> 00:41:28,240
An apology?

551
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:30,080
Sorry, what apology?

552
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:32,680
Oh, pardon.

553
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:34,120
You are right.

554
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:36,160
Ateş Karahan never apologizes.

555
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:43,760
Even his gift is not for you,
you still went to dinner with him.

556
00:41:47,440 --> 00:41:49,040
And you were clearly having a good time.

557
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:52,760
Meeting up?

558
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:54,760
Having fun?

559
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:01,640
Do you know I do not care
anymore what you believe or not?

560
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:05,160
I will not explain a single
word to you from now on.

561
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,480
You should care.

562
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:23,080
Because you are my wife.

563
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:39,760
The more I try to be patient and
explain, the more pointless it gets.

564
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:42,120
You want more.

565
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:48,680
Then why did you go to dinner with him?

566
00:42:50,840 --> 00:42:53,040
Why should I answer you again and again?

567
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:55,360
What I say has no meaning for you.

568
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:57,680
It is like all my words hit a wall.

569
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,640
I know, because you will not listen.

570
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:01,880
I am talking for nothing.

571
00:43:02,160 --> 00:43:03,680
We are stuck in a vicious cycle.

572
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:05,696
The same things, the same
things again and again.

573
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:06,720
I am sick of it now.

574
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:08,080
Okay? I am sick of it.

575
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:14,680
You will explain.

576
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:15,920
We will talk.

577
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,000
What am I supposed to explain?

578
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:22,080
Why should I?

579
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,840
I have been trying to talk to
you all day, you did not listen.

580
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,920
Now I do not want to talk to you.

581
00:43:32,680 --> 00:43:34,760
All I want is to get rid
of you as soon as possible.

582
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,200
What am I doing like this?

583
00:44:52,880 --> 00:44:54,080
What is happening to me?

584
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,080
Do not keep stalling me, Nezir.

585
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:07,080
I am not buying these moves.

586
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:08,840
We made a deal.

587
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:09,920
I did my part.

588
00:45:10,160 --> 00:45:11,160
Now it is your turn.

589
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:13,320
But I did nothing wrong in what happened.

590
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:15,440
Damn it, a ton of my money is gone.

591
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,600
That is not my problem.

592
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:18,800
I cleaned up your mess.

593
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:21,680
You were crying Mercan,
Mercan, and I saved you.

594
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:23,240
I am the one who got burned.

595
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:27,000
I swear, Haydar,

596
00:45:27,440 --> 00:45:30,760
you are not a man who would care about
your daughter turning her back on you.

597
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:34,240
Are you making fun of me, Nezir?

598
00:45:35,120 --> 00:45:37,800
Did you think you could put me in
the crosshairs and get rid of me?

599
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:41,560
Try to relax a little.

600
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:44,960
Look, we are both targets.

601
00:45:47,440 --> 00:45:49,600
All you care about is Mercan.

602
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,760
I have only one concern, and that is Ateş.

603
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:54,480
I have some delicate plans about him.

604
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:56,640
That is why I need money.

605
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:59,520
More than anything, I need power, got it?

606
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:02,920
You will do exactly what I tell you.

607
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:05,920
We will.

608
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:11,880
We will.

609
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:41,160
Guess who I am.

610
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:44,480
Berat, are you a kid or what?

611
00:46:44,520 --> 00:46:45,520
What are you doing?

612
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:47,240
Zehra, you really hit hard.

613
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:49,440
I am sure I cracked a rib or something.

614
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:51,360
I am sorry.

615
00:46:57,440 --> 00:46:59,040
I am fine, do not worry.

616
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:01,800
We will get caught by
someone, what are you doing?

617
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:03,920
We do not need to hide it, Zehra.

618
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:05,320
Let everyone find out.

619
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:07,879
Do not. Do not tell anyone, okay?

620
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,160
No one must know, Berat.

621
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:10,880
Why?

622
00:47:13,640 --> 00:47:16,040
Your mother and your
sibling do not like me much.

623
00:47:16,720 --> 00:47:17,760
They are right anyway.

624
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:20,720
You know we got off on the wrong foot.

625
00:47:21,440 --> 00:47:22,440
Yes.

626
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:25,200
If we rush, they will try to split us up.

627
00:47:26,640 --> 00:47:28,880
So let me win them over first.

628
00:47:29,400 --> 00:47:31,120
Let them get to know me better.

629
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:34,760
Right.

630
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:35,800
You are right.

631
00:47:36,160 --> 00:47:37,519
Sure, I will take the
castle from the inside.

632
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:38,160
Yes.

633
00:47:38,520 --> 00:47:39,320
Very logical.

634
00:47:39,520 --> 00:47:40,520
Sure.

635
00:47:40,720 --> 00:47:43,400
Very logical, I really liked this.

636
00:47:43,680 --> 00:47:45,520
Once they get to know
you, they will like you.

637
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:46,560
I mean.

638
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:48,800
You are not exactly an
unlikable girl anyway.

639
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:54,760
Okay.

640
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:56,080
I will be around.

641
00:47:56,600 --> 00:47:57,600
Okay.

642
00:47:57,640 --> 00:47:58,280
Good luck.

643
00:47:58,480 --> 00:47:59,560
Okay, I am sorry.

644
00:47:59,840 --> 00:48:00,960
No, it is nothing important.

645
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:02,800
But you hit hard.

646
00:48:36,200 --> 00:48:37,520
Is this what you are looking for?

647
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:00,680
I caught Nermin here.

648
00:49:01,960 --> 00:49:03,720
They found the key in the garden.

649
00:49:04,840 --> 00:49:06,880
What if Ateş had gone
inside and seen everything?

650
00:49:12,720 --> 00:49:14,440
You have been very distracted lately.

651
00:49:14,480 --> 00:49:16,840
You are doing unexpected
things because of Mercan.

652
00:49:19,800 --> 00:49:20,800
Mother Müzeyyen.

653
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:27,840
Let’s not talk about this now.

654
00:49:28,400 --> 00:49:29,400
It is not the time.

655
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:33,000
When she is mentioned,
you lose your reason.

656
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:36,720
Especially since Mercan was shot,
you've started to look at her differently.

657
00:49:42,080 --> 00:49:43,560
I am a woman too, Ateş, I understand.

658
00:49:44,360 --> 00:49:47,360
The way a man looks at a
woman, the feelings he carries...

659
00:49:47,400 --> 00:49:48,400
Enough, mother Müzeyyen.

660
00:49:52,960 --> 00:49:53,960
Stop right there.

661
00:50:00,120 --> 00:50:01,120
Stop right there.

662
00:50:05,800 --> 00:50:08,560
That girl is making you
make mistakes, my son.

663
00:50:09,520 --> 00:50:12,400
You act with anger without
researching or thinking.

664
00:50:13,400 --> 00:50:15,760
Look, you got angry at Nezir
and went and bought a company.

665
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:18,040
You almost lost your life.

666
00:50:26,360 --> 00:50:27,600
This path is not right.

667
00:50:28,880 --> 00:50:31,520
If this continues, Aslı
and Cemal will get hurt too.

668
00:50:36,920 --> 00:50:38,840
There is no room for weakness on your path.

669
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:45,199
If you do not cut your
ties with that girl...

670
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:47,040
you will throw all of us into the fire.

671
00:51:23,520 --> 00:51:26,440
The way a man looks at a
woman, the feelings he carries...

672
00:51:26,480 --> 00:51:27,720
Enough, mother Müzeyyen.

673
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:50,920
When she is mentioned,
you lose your reason.

674
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:54,800
Especially since Mercan was shot,
you've started to look at her differently.

675
00:54:39,040 --> 00:54:40,400
Are you okay?

676
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:42,000
Is something wrong?

677
00:54:42,440 --> 00:54:43,440
I am fine.

678
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:06,280
There is no room for weakness on your path.

679
00:55:07,400 --> 00:55:11,280
If you don't cut your ties with that girl,
you will throw all of us into the fire.

680
00:55:26,040 --> 00:55:27,800
That will not happen.

681
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:44,520
There is no place for her in my heart.

682
00:55:45,080 --> 00:55:49,360
No... No... No!

683
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:23,440
Why did you call me here?

684
00:58:55,960 --> 00:58:58,000
You are leaving here right now.

685
01:00:08,720 --> 01:00:11,080
You're leaving here right now.

686
01:00:17,320 --> 01:00:18,400
What are you talking about?

687
01:00:22,920 --> 01:00:24,080
I said you're leaving here.

688
01:00:26,760 --> 01:00:27,760
Leaving where?

689
01:00:28,200 --> 01:00:29,280
What are you talking about?

690
01:00:29,680 --> 01:00:30,680
Have you lost your mind?

691
01:00:32,560 --> 01:00:34,000
I have.

692
01:00:36,760 --> 01:00:38,280
Everything is arranged.

693
01:00:41,320 --> 01:00:43,600
You'll stay in London until
the divorce period is over.

694
01:00:53,880 --> 01:00:56,880
Your plane ticket and all the information
you need are inside the envelope.

695
01:01:08,880 --> 01:01:10,160
I need to stay away from you.

696
01:01:28,360 --> 01:01:29,400
I don't understand you.

697
01:01:33,720 --> 01:01:34,480
Where is this coming from?

698
01:01:34,481 --> 01:01:35,880
Why would I go to London?

699
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:39,040
That's how it has to be.

700
01:01:41,560 --> 01:01:43,080
That's exactly what I want to know.

701
01:01:43,120 --> 01:01:44,400
Why does it have to be that way?

702
01:01:48,680 --> 01:01:50,000
Because I want it that way.

703
01:01:52,760 --> 01:01:53,800
You want it that way.

704
01:01:55,200 --> 01:01:56,200
Is that it?

705
01:01:57,960 --> 01:01:58,960
Yes.

706
01:02:00,120 --> 01:02:01,120
This.

707
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:10,200
If I tell you to go, you'll go.

708
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:17,800
What if I refuse?

709
01:02:30,560 --> 01:02:32,200
Do you remember the contract between us?

710
01:02:34,200 --> 01:02:35,640
How could I forget?

711
01:02:37,040 --> 01:02:39,520
My 187 days of captivity started that day.

712
01:02:42,760 --> 01:02:43,760
There.

713
01:02:46,320 --> 01:02:48,601
If you don't go to London, I
will terminate the contract.

714
01:02:57,520 --> 01:02:59,440
You'll be forced to stay
married to me for life.

715
01:03:02,360 --> 01:03:04,480
You and your family will lose everything.

716
01:03:26,960 --> 01:03:29,320
Why are you doing this to me?

717
01:03:39,320 --> 01:03:42,200
Because I...

718
01:03:51,040 --> 01:03:53,160
Because I... What?

719
01:03:57,320 --> 01:03:58,800
I can't see you.

720
01:04:00,240 --> 01:04:02,720
Because every time, I lose to those eyes.

721
01:04:10,000 --> 01:04:12,000
Because I don't want to see you ever again.

722
01:04:17,160 --> 01:04:18,720
I don't want you by my side.

723
01:04:29,840 --> 01:04:31,880
Did I make myself clear?

724
01:04:38,920 --> 01:04:40,480
How you shatter my heart like this?

725
01:04:42,040 --> 01:04:43,280
What did I ever do to you?

726
01:04:44,360 --> 01:04:46,880
Your tears are flowing because of me again.

727
01:04:54,640 --> 01:04:55,920
How am I supposed to leave?

728
01:04:56,200 --> 01:05:00,600
This mansion, my family, you...

729
01:05:05,520 --> 01:05:08,600
You need to go so I can keep going.

730
01:06:50,440 --> 01:06:52,800
Seeing you like this hurts.

731
01:06:54,680 --> 01:06:56,480
But I have no choice.

732
01:07:41,280 --> 01:07:42,640
Go. Right now.

733
01:07:45,840 --> 01:07:47,160
Get out of my life.

734
01:08:39,040 --> 01:08:40,840
So you told her.

735
01:08:42,400 --> 01:08:43,400
How did you know?

736
01:08:45,000 --> 01:08:46,440
I mean, how did you know I told her?

737
01:08:46,600 --> 01:08:48,881
You don’t need to be a fortune
teller to figure that out.

738
01:08:50,400 --> 01:08:51,680
One look at your face is enough.

739
01:08:53,240 --> 01:08:54,280
What are you getting at?

740
01:08:56,000 --> 01:08:57,000
Let me warn you first.

741
01:08:57,240 --> 01:08:59,120
You’re not going to like
what I’m about to say.

742
01:09:01,440 --> 01:09:03,640
Right now I see an Ateş
who’s completely falling apart.

743
01:09:04,600 --> 01:09:06,520
I think we both know exactly why.

744
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:10,280
Then if you were going to be this
upset, why did you tell her to go?

745
01:09:12,040 --> 01:09:13,160
What upset?

746
01:09:14,120 --> 01:09:15,176
What are you talking about?

747
01:09:15,200 --> 01:09:17,280
I only did what I had to do.

748
01:09:17,680 --> 01:09:18,840
Alright then. Fine.

749
01:09:19,000 --> 01:09:20,000
I won’t say anything.

750
01:09:21,360 --> 01:09:22,360
Fair enough.

751
01:09:23,600 --> 01:09:25,080
So what did Mercan say to your offer?

752
01:09:28,080 --> 01:09:29,240
She didn’t say anything.

753
01:09:32,240 --> 01:09:33,080
I saw her a moment ago.

754
01:09:33,200 --> 01:09:34,640
She was pretty upset too.

755
01:09:39,720 --> 01:09:40,400
So what are you going to do now?

756
01:09:40,480 --> 01:09:42,040
Grab her by the arm and drag her there?

757
01:09:43,720 --> 01:09:45,680
She has to go.

758
01:09:47,040 --> 01:09:48,160
She will go, no matter what.

759
01:09:56,440 --> 01:09:58,920
I’ll give instructions
to the kitchen for dinner.

760
01:09:59,000 --> 01:10:00,080
What would you like to eat?

761
01:10:03,400 --> 01:10:06,280
Honestly you’ll be surprised, but
for the first time I have no appetite.

762
01:10:07,160 --> 01:10:08,160
What’s wrong with her?

763
01:10:17,440 --> 01:10:19,480
When do you think Malik will propose to me?

764
01:10:21,440 --> 01:10:23,240
Since he bought the
ring, probably tomorrow.

765
01:10:24,440 --> 01:10:26,640
Maybe even today.

766
01:10:28,000 --> 01:10:29,520
He wouldn’t do it on the fly.

767
01:10:33,640 --> 01:10:35,800
He’s definitely planning
something romantic for me.

768
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:39,800
Malik?

769
01:10:40,200 --> 01:10:41,240
Çiçek, what are you doing?

770
01:10:42,400 --> 01:10:43,400
Nothing, just that.

771
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:44,720
Is anyone around?

772
01:10:44,840 --> 01:10:45,840
No no, we’re good.

773
01:10:46,320 --> 01:10:48,160
Were you talking to yourself?

774
01:10:48,800 --> 01:10:49,800
Me?

775
01:10:50,680 --> 01:10:53,920
No, I was, uh, thinking.

776
01:10:57,760 --> 01:11:00,760
So in a way, you were talking to me.

777
01:11:01,600 --> 01:11:02,880
What were you saying then?

778
01:11:03,640 --> 01:11:08,000
I was saying, you seem like
you want to tell me something.

779
01:11:08,360 --> 01:11:11,800
Or like you want to ask me something.

780
01:11:12,920 --> 01:11:15,520
No Çiçek, where did that come from now?

781
01:11:16,440 --> 01:11:17,440
I don’t know.

782
01:11:18,240 --> 01:11:21,480
Your mood, your behavior,
that’s how it felt to me.

783
01:11:21,760 --> 01:11:23,759
Like you want to tell me something.

784
01:11:23,760 --> 01:11:26,760
More like you want to ask me something.

785
01:11:27,800 --> 01:11:29,200
Don’t hold back, go on, ask.

786
01:11:29,840 --> 01:11:31,920
I’ll gladly answer.

787
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:34,760
Çiçek, why are you acting strange?

788
01:11:35,440 --> 01:11:36,680
I wasn’t going to say anything.

789
01:11:37,080 --> 01:11:38,920
I’m talking nonsense
again, nonsense, alright.

790
01:11:39,120 --> 01:11:41,080
You know me, my usual self.

791
01:11:43,720 --> 01:11:45,400
Are we meeting tonight then?

792
01:11:47,960 --> 01:11:48,960
We are.

793
01:11:49,240 --> 01:11:50,360
Why wouldn’t we, sweetheart?

794
01:11:51,080 --> 01:11:52,080
Where will we meet?

795
01:11:52,840 --> 01:11:54,080
Some fancy place?

796
01:11:55,040 --> 01:11:56,040
What should I wear?

797
01:11:56,400 --> 01:11:58,080
Something elegant, or something simple?

798
01:11:59,080 --> 01:12:00,320
Don’t ask me.

799
01:12:00,840 --> 01:12:01,840
Wear whatever you like.

800
01:12:03,240 --> 01:12:05,400
You’re beautiful no matter what, Çiçek.

801
01:12:07,120 --> 01:12:09,600
Then I’ll take care
of things in the kitchen.

802
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:10,440
Let’s start getting ready.

803
01:12:10,520 --> 01:12:11,920
Isn’t it too early?

804
01:12:12,080 --> 01:12:13,480
There’s a lot of time till evening.

805
01:12:13,920 --> 01:12:15,680
We’re already late, don’t be silly.

806
01:12:16,360 --> 01:12:19,840
There’s the dress, the
shoes, the hair, the makeup.

807
01:12:20,720 --> 01:12:22,800
I have so much to do, I won’t make it.

808
01:12:23,320 --> 01:12:24,520
I won’t make it.

809
01:12:25,840 --> 01:12:27,136
Come on, you go too, don’t stand here.

810
01:12:27,160 --> 01:12:28,160
My mom will come.

811
01:12:29,200 --> 01:12:30,200
Go on, go.

812
01:12:49,480 --> 01:12:51,000
We’re having coffee with your father.

813
01:12:51,480 --> 01:12:53,080
I’ll tell them to make some for you too.

814
01:13:00,160 --> 01:13:01,400
Why the long face, my girl?

815
01:13:02,520 --> 01:13:03,760
Did something upset you?

816
01:13:05,320 --> 01:13:06,320
Nothing.

817
01:13:11,280 --> 01:13:13,080
Would I not know my own daughter?

818
01:13:13,720 --> 01:13:15,760
Something clearly
happened, come on, tell me.

819
01:13:16,720 --> 01:13:19,600
My girl, did Ateş do something again?

820
01:13:22,280 --> 01:13:23,680
He wants me to go to London.

821
01:13:25,160 --> 01:13:26,160
What?

822
01:13:27,400 --> 01:13:28,400
London?

823
01:13:31,760 --> 01:13:34,680
What’s his problem this
time, where did this come from?

824
01:13:35,840 --> 01:13:36,840
I don’t know.

825
01:13:37,840 --> 01:13:40,400
He said you’ll stay there
until the 187 days are over.

826
01:13:41,760 --> 01:13:45,400
I told you, my girl, this man is
doing everything he can to tear us apart.

827
01:13:45,960 --> 01:13:47,520
You must see now I was right.

828
01:13:48,600 --> 01:13:49,600
Is this man crazy?

829
01:13:50,160 --> 01:13:51,960
What nonsense, why would you go?

830
01:13:53,840 --> 01:13:55,400
He doesn’t want to see me.

831
01:13:57,840 --> 01:13:58,840
What a load of nonsense.

832
01:13:59,200 --> 01:14:00,200
Then let him go himself.

833
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:02,280
You’re not going anywhere.

834
01:14:03,080 --> 01:14:05,520
We’re not about to hand the
field over to the Karahans.

835
01:14:06,560 --> 01:14:07,560
You’re my daughter.

836
01:14:08,120 --> 01:14:09,360
Haydar Yıldırım’s daughter.

837
01:14:09,680 --> 01:14:12,560
You’re not going anywhere just
because Mr. Ateş’s royal mood demands it.

838
01:14:19,960 --> 01:14:23,640
Mercan, listen, if want too,
wipe this out of your mind.

839
01:14:24,800 --> 01:14:26,000
Where we are, you’re there.

840
01:14:31,360 --> 01:14:34,320
If I don’t go, he’ll
terminate the contract.

841
01:14:39,120 --> 01:14:40,160
The deal will fall apart.

842
01:14:41,400 --> 01:14:44,160
And when the 187 days are
over, he won’t divorce me.

843
01:14:47,800 --> 01:14:49,080
We’ll lose everything.

844
01:14:50,480 --> 01:14:50,800
What?

845
01:14:51,480 --> 01:14:53,520
How? What are you saying?

846
01:14:55,400 --> 01:14:56,440
Can he do that, Haydar?

847
01:14:59,640 --> 01:15:01,240
If he wants to, he will.

848
01:15:01,880 --> 01:15:05,240
Everything we’re supposed to take
back at the end, goes to Ateş Karahan.

849
01:15:05,920 --> 01:15:07,440
We’ll be left with nothing at all.

850
01:15:08,440 --> 01:15:11,320
I told you, my girl, I told you
this man is looking for an excuse.

851
01:15:14,400 --> 01:15:16,760
He’d throw us out on the
street penniless without blinking.

852
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:22,400
You wouldn’t let something like
that happen, would you my girl?

853
01:15:25,520 --> 01:15:26,920
Are you saying I should go, mom?

854
01:15:29,280 --> 01:15:30,560
The decision is yours.

855
01:15:32,000 --> 01:15:34,800
But the right thing is
for you to go, isn’t it?

856
01:15:38,920 --> 01:15:39,920
So I should go.

857
01:15:43,120 --> 01:15:45,560
When you think about it,
it even sounds reasonable.

858
01:15:47,600 --> 01:15:50,640
And once you’re in London, you won’t
have to put up with Ateş’s face either.

859
01:15:51,440 --> 01:15:53,120
It’ll be a change for you.

860
01:15:54,040 --> 01:15:55,040
Isn’t that right Haydar?

861
01:15:58,200 --> 01:15:59,280
I get you.

862
01:16:01,080 --> 01:16:02,320
Why I even bothered explaining.

863
01:16:04,080 --> 01:16:07,040
This isn’t worse than staying married
to a man you don’t even know, is it?

864
01:16:24,760 --> 01:16:25,440
I’m heading out.

865
01:16:25,520 --> 01:16:26,520
Where are you going?

866
01:16:27,240 --> 01:16:28,480
We got bad news.

867
01:16:28,560 --> 01:16:30,640
At least let me do something
good to make up for it.

868
01:16:43,080 --> 01:16:44,080
We’re exhausted though.

869
01:16:44,880 --> 01:16:45,880
Aren’t we?

870
01:16:46,640 --> 01:16:47,640
You bet, brother.

871
01:16:48,680 --> 01:16:49,680
We’re dead on our feet.

872
01:16:51,360 --> 01:16:52,400
Let me tell you something.

873
01:16:52,920 --> 01:16:54,920
All of this is always
Müzeyyen Hanım’s inventions.

874
01:16:55,000 --> 01:16:56,000
Exactly.

875
01:17:03,000 --> 01:17:04,280
Look at the time...

876
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:06,320
and the work still isn’t done.

877
01:17:06,960 --> 01:17:08,720
Honestly, at this rate
I’m going to be late.

878
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:12,240
Go on, you go. Don’t wait.

879
01:17:12,280 --> 01:17:13,280
I’ll handle the rest.

880
01:17:13,720 --> 01:17:14,920
No, that won’t do.

881
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:18,520
Brother, go, I swear if you
don’t go you’ll see death.

882
01:17:19,160 --> 01:17:19,560
Come on.

883
01:17:19,880 --> 01:17:20,880
Astaghfirullah.

884
01:17:20,960 --> 01:17:22,440
What kind of talk is that, brother?

885
01:17:22,600 --> 01:17:23,600
God forbid, son.

886
01:17:23,960 --> 01:17:25,176
Would something like
that happen between us?

887
01:17:25,200 --> 01:17:26,296
I’ll take care of it anyway.

888
01:17:26,320 --> 01:17:27,896
Almost done. Just a couple of things left.

889
01:17:27,920 --> 01:17:28,560
I’ll gather them up right away.

890
01:17:28,880 --> 01:17:29,880
If you say so.

891
01:17:30,120 --> 01:17:31,616
Exactly, exactly, swear to God, come on.

892
01:17:31,640 --> 01:17:32,160
Eyvallah.

893
01:17:32,520 --> 01:17:34,360
Then I’ll take these and go.

894
01:17:34,560 --> 01:17:35,560
Alright. Alright.

895
01:17:35,880 --> 01:17:36,200
Come on.

896
01:17:36,360 --> 01:17:37,360
Then come on.

897
01:17:37,760 --> 01:17:38,360
Easy work.

898
01:17:38,640 --> 01:17:40,040
Eyvallah brother, thanks.

899
01:17:46,600 --> 01:17:47,760
Easy work, son.

900
01:17:48,440 --> 01:17:49,000
Thanks mom.

901
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:50,160
Isn’t it finished yet?

902
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:52,000
Almost.

903
01:17:52,480 --> 01:17:54,120
Come on, take a break and have some tea.

904
01:17:56,080 --> 01:17:57,519
I swear you brought it at the perfect time.

905
01:17:57,520 --> 01:17:59,560
This will do me good, look, look.

906
01:18:01,920 --> 01:18:04,240
I swear mom, this felt so
good after all that exhaustion.

907
01:18:06,880 --> 01:18:09,039
Enjoy it, son, enjoy it, but...

908
01:18:09,040 --> 01:18:10,560
Something caught my attention.

909
01:18:11,080 --> 01:18:13,840
Since when did you get this
close with Malik, mashallah?

910
01:18:15,640 --> 01:18:17,720
Mom, we work at the same place.

911
01:18:18,160 --> 01:18:19,560
We’re together every day.

912
01:18:20,360 --> 01:18:21,480
He’s like a brother to me.

913
01:18:23,800 --> 01:18:25,400
Like your brother, huh?

914
01:18:25,520 --> 01:18:25,840
Yeah.

915
01:18:26,120 --> 01:18:27,200
Well I’ll be damned.

916
01:18:27,400 --> 01:18:29,720
Son, we don’t know anything about this boy.

917
01:18:29,960 --> 01:18:31,576
Who is he, what is he,
where did he come from?

918
01:18:31,600 --> 01:18:33,880
Alright, we know he came
from Egypt, we know that.

919
01:18:34,320 --> 01:18:35,800
But other than that, we know nothing.

920
01:18:36,920 --> 01:18:41,640
Honestly mom, where he came from,
who he is, what he is, I don’t know.

921
01:18:42,720 --> 01:18:44,040
Like a brother, that’s all.

922
01:18:44,560 --> 01:18:45,600
Malik is a good kid.

923
01:18:46,040 --> 01:18:47,040
A decent man.

924
01:18:47,800 --> 01:18:48,960
I’m serious.

925
01:18:49,720 --> 01:18:52,840
Alright son, but how did
this boy pay off that debt?

926
01:18:53,120 --> 01:18:55,440
Isn’t he a chauffeur working
on salary in this mansion?

927
01:18:56,040 --> 01:18:57,120
How did he pay that debt?

928
01:18:58,920 --> 01:19:01,199
Am I the only one whose
mind doesn’t grasp this?

929
01:19:01,200 --> 01:19:02,680
Am I the only one who doesn’t get it?

930
01:19:02,760 --> 01:19:04,160
Honestly it feels strange to me.

931
01:19:04,840 --> 01:19:05,880
I don’t get it.

932
01:19:06,480 --> 01:19:08,560
Listen to your mother.

933
01:19:09,080 --> 01:19:12,120
Don’t trust people you
don’t know, not all at once.

934
01:19:13,240 --> 01:19:16,560
I’m leaving, I have work at the mansion.

935
01:19:17,080 --> 01:19:18,080
Listen to your mother.

936
01:20:09,840 --> 01:20:10,840
Why?

937
01:20:15,360 --> 01:20:16,360
Don’t ask.

938
01:20:17,200 --> 01:20:19,160
Just don’t ask, just go.

939
01:20:30,840 --> 01:20:32,040
I can’t stand that look.

940
01:20:42,760 --> 01:20:45,320
Where did this London business come from?

941
01:20:46,120 --> 01:20:47,320
Why do you want me to go?

942
01:20:49,040 --> 01:20:50,320
I told you.

943
01:20:51,920 --> 01:20:53,480
I don’t want to see you.

944
01:20:57,840 --> 01:20:59,560
I don’t want you near me.

945
01:21:00,160 --> 01:21:01,440
Why did you change like this?

946
01:21:04,080 --> 01:21:05,960
How many more times do I have to repeat it?

947
01:21:09,640 --> 01:21:11,280
What did I ever do to you?

948
01:21:14,520 --> 01:21:15,840
This conversation is over.

949
01:21:20,400 --> 01:21:22,080
You really don’t want to see me at all?

950
01:21:22,320 --> 01:21:24,120
You hate me this much?

951
01:21:26,560 --> 01:21:28,320
Didn’t you want to get rid of me?

952
01:21:35,880 --> 01:21:37,200
You said it just today.

953
01:21:38,120 --> 01:21:39,280
What are you questioning now?

954
01:21:41,760 --> 01:21:46,040
Alright, I said it but... You
took advantage of it, didn’t you?

955
01:21:49,240 --> 01:21:51,160
Works out for you anyway.

956
01:21:57,440 --> 01:21:59,520
Aren’t you counting the
days till you get rid of me?

957
01:22:00,960 --> 01:22:02,840
You were ticking them
off one by one, remember?

958
01:22:04,080 --> 01:22:08,240
Now that I told you to
go... why are you complaining?

959
01:22:16,000 --> 01:22:17,760
Is it because Nezir isn’t around?

960
01:22:18,240 --> 01:22:20,280
Otherwise you’d run off
without a second thought.

961
01:22:20,720 --> 01:22:22,680
You go to dinner every
time he calls anyway.

962
01:22:26,640 --> 01:22:28,240
Maybe Nezir would even follow you there.

963
01:22:28,640 --> 01:22:29,920
But I won’t allow even that.

964
01:22:30,120 --> 01:22:31,200
I’ll crush your dreams.

965
01:22:39,920 --> 01:22:41,160
Nezir is the problem, isn’t he?

966
01:22:55,160 --> 01:22:56,440
Watch your mouth.

967
01:22:57,000 --> 01:22:58,360
You can’t talk to me like that.

968
01:23:18,360 --> 01:23:19,600
What are you saying, Ateş?

969
01:23:20,960 --> 01:23:23,040
Why can’t you get this
Nezir thing out of your head?

970
01:24:04,160 --> 01:24:06,040
What a beautiful day.

971
01:24:06,520 --> 01:24:07,520
The air smells great too.

972
01:24:07,640 --> 01:24:08,640
Why are you home?

973
01:24:09,560 --> 01:24:11,320
I see you’re in high spirits.

974
01:24:11,480 --> 01:24:12,480
What’s going on?

975
01:24:15,160 --> 01:24:16,160
You’re right.

976
01:24:17,440 --> 01:24:19,920
I haven’t felt this
cheerful in a long time.

977
01:24:21,400 --> 01:24:23,800
Because Ateş is shipping
Mercan off to London.

978
01:24:25,200 --> 01:24:26,320
Sending her to London?

979
01:24:27,520 --> 01:24:28,520
Why?

980
01:24:29,640 --> 01:24:31,319
Talking to Ateş paid off.

981
01:24:31,320 --> 01:24:33,960
He finally saw the light.

982
01:24:34,280 --> 01:24:35,840
We’re getting rid of this little snake.

983
01:24:37,600 --> 01:24:40,640
He has feelings big enough
for Mercan to send her far away.

984
01:24:41,880 --> 01:24:43,320
What are you talking about, girl?

985
01:24:45,120 --> 01:24:46,760
Of course he has feelings.

986
01:24:47,200 --> 01:24:48,520
But look at it.

987
01:24:48,600 --> 01:24:49,600
Ateş is sending her away.

988
01:24:50,000 --> 01:24:51,000
Don’t you get it?

989
01:24:51,520 --> 01:24:53,880
I get it, but you’re
the one who doesn’t, mom.

990
01:24:56,480 --> 01:24:57,640
What’s gotten into you, Aslı?

991
01:24:57,880 --> 01:24:58,880
What’s with the attitude?

992
01:24:59,560 --> 01:25:02,200
I thought you’d be happy she was leaving.

993
01:25:03,200 --> 01:25:04,200
I was wrong.

994
01:25:04,640 --> 01:25:05,640
Very wrong.

995
01:25:06,040 --> 01:25:08,000
We won’t get rid of that girl so easily.

996
01:25:32,920 --> 01:25:34,080
You made the right decision.

997
01:25:39,720 --> 01:25:41,280
Don’t look at me like that.

998
01:25:42,000 --> 01:25:43,400
You have no choice but to sign.

999
01:25:57,360 --> 01:25:59,280
May our partnership be blessed.

1000
01:26:00,720 --> 01:26:01,720
Partner.

1001
01:26:02,680 --> 01:26:05,600
You might feel like you lost.

1002
01:26:06,840 --> 01:26:09,640
But you know you’ll profit from this.

1003
01:26:18,240 --> 01:26:19,880
The man practically took over my company.

1004
01:26:28,000 --> 01:26:30,200
Ateş is sending Mercan to London.

1005
01:26:32,200 --> 01:26:33,200
London?

1006
01:26:37,680 --> 01:26:39,200
Now my day just got better.

1007
01:26:49,240 --> 01:26:51,360
Good riddance before
it blew up in our faces.

1008
01:26:57,520 --> 01:27:00,840
Oh oh oh.

1009
01:27:02,400 --> 01:27:07,679
But honestly I don’t know
which one to deal with anymore...

1010
01:27:07,680 --> 01:27:10,440
And this Çiçek picked the
perfect time to disappear.

1011
01:27:14,320 --> 01:27:16,240
Don’t hang around, I’m handling this.

1012
01:27:17,680 --> 01:27:19,600
I can help, we’ll handle it together.

1013
01:27:32,080 --> 01:27:33,640
I’ll unload the machine.

1014
01:27:33,800 --> 01:27:36,000
You take care of the other things, alright?

1015
01:27:44,400 --> 01:27:45,400
Mom.

1016
01:27:46,120 --> 01:27:47,200
What is it, Insallah?

1017
01:27:47,480 --> 01:27:47,840
I don’t get it.

1018
01:27:48,440 --> 01:27:49,440
What happened to her?

1019
01:27:50,160 --> 01:27:51,160
I don’t get it either.

1020
01:27:51,600 --> 01:27:53,080
Did a stone fall on her head or what?

1021
01:27:53,920 --> 01:27:55,080
I don’t know either, my girl.

1022
01:27:56,720 --> 01:27:57,720
What did you do?

1023
01:28:03,000 --> 01:28:05,720
Çiçek, it’s hot, be careful.

1024
01:28:15,480 --> 01:28:17,320
Zehra.

1025
01:28:17,840 --> 01:28:19,640
While you’re there,
grab me a glass of water.

1026
01:28:22,040 --> 01:28:23,040
Sure.

1027
01:28:40,440 --> 01:28:41,440
Thanks, dear.

1028
01:28:41,800 --> 01:28:42,840
Enjoy it, sweetheart.

1029
01:29:15,120 --> 01:29:16,760
You scared the hell out of me.

1030
01:29:16,800 --> 01:29:17,800
You’re crazy.

1031
01:29:18,480 --> 01:29:19,480
Listen to me.

1032
01:29:19,720 --> 01:29:21,240
Hearing it on the phone wasn’t enough.

1033
01:29:22,200 --> 01:29:23,840
I want to hear it with my own ears.

1034
01:29:24,560 --> 01:29:26,200
Is Ateş sending Mercan to London?

1035
01:29:28,880 --> 01:29:30,000
This is great news.

1036
01:29:30,880 --> 01:29:32,520
I haven’t been this happy in a long time.

1037
01:29:34,160 --> 01:29:36,480
You’re all so stupid.

1038
01:29:36,880 --> 01:29:38,000
You too.

1039
01:29:38,360 --> 01:29:40,560
Right now you look so pathetic in my eyes.

1040
01:29:40,880 --> 01:29:42,159
You’re no different from an insect.

1041
01:29:42,160 --> 01:29:44,120
Watch your mouth.

1042
01:29:44,400 --> 01:29:45,880
How dare you talk to me like that?

1043
01:29:46,320 --> 01:29:48,280
You get a grip yourself.

1044
01:29:48,720 --> 01:29:50,960
Ateş sending Mercan away
is nothing to celebrate.

1045
01:29:51,680 --> 01:29:53,440
I can’t be the only one seeing this.

1046
01:29:54,240 --> 01:29:55,440
What nonsense are you talking?

1047
01:29:56,280 --> 01:29:57,560
Why wouldn’t I be happy?

1048
01:29:58,840 --> 01:30:00,760
Ateş is sending her
because he doesn’t love her.

1049
01:30:01,240 --> 01:30:03,160
And they won’t be glued
to each other anymore.

1050
01:30:04,400 --> 01:30:06,040
That’s all I want, dear Aslı.

1051
01:30:07,760 --> 01:30:09,920
Ateş isn’t sending Mercan
because he doesn’t love her.

1052
01:30:10,320 --> 01:30:11,840
He’s sending her because he’s jealous.

1053
01:30:13,640 --> 01:30:15,560
Jealous of you.

1054
01:30:15,640 --> 01:30:16,680
Got it?

1055
01:30:22,360 --> 01:30:23,360
Jealous?

1056
01:30:24,360 --> 01:30:26,440
That’s why he wants her gone?

1057
01:30:27,480 --> 01:30:29,000
Does that mean he loves her?

1058
01:30:30,200 --> 01:30:31,200
You finally got it.

1059
01:30:37,280 --> 01:30:39,960
Damn, I thought it was just a power move.

1060
01:30:40,600 --> 01:30:41,960
Just to spite me.

1061
01:30:42,640 --> 01:30:44,200
I know Ateş.

1062
01:30:44,600 --> 01:30:46,440
Let me tell you what will happen.

1063
01:30:47,320 --> 01:30:49,360
Being apart will bind him even tighter.

1064
01:30:50,160 --> 01:30:52,200
Not being able to reunite
will break him even more.

1065
01:30:52,640 --> 01:30:54,280
Ateş’s mind will always be on Mercan.

1066
01:30:56,360 --> 01:31:00,400
Every day he’s apart from Mercan, he’ll
think all the things they couldn't do.

1067
01:31:01,280 --> 01:31:03,240
His love will grow tenfold.

1068
01:31:04,200 --> 01:31:06,080
Why are you telling me all this, girl?

1069
01:31:07,320 --> 01:31:11,159
I don’t care what Ateş feels
or thinks, it means nothing to me.

1070
01:31:11,160 --> 01:31:13,200
He can die of love for all I care.

1071
01:31:16,120 --> 01:31:18,800
The only thing I care about
is Mercan being away from him.

1072
01:31:21,480 --> 01:31:23,680
And who knows, maybe I’ll go to London too.

1073
01:31:25,320 --> 01:31:29,280
Of course you have the assumption
that Mercan doesn’t love Ateş, right?

1074
01:31:31,680 --> 01:31:37,000
If you used this a little, you’d
know distance means nothing to lovers.

1075
01:31:37,400 --> 01:31:42,320
But what would you know about love...
All you know is brute force, hostility.

1076
01:31:44,120 --> 01:31:45,480
I won’t strain my jaw any further.

1077
01:31:46,520 --> 01:31:47,520
It’s a waste of my time.

1078
01:33:07,000 --> 01:33:08,520
You’re leaving here right now.

1079
01:33:17,240 --> 01:33:18,240
She has to go...

1080
01:33:20,160 --> 01:33:21,160
This is how it should be.

1081
01:34:29,160 --> 01:34:32,160
Looks like neither of us can move on.

1082
01:34:37,320 --> 01:34:43,240
You and I both need to go our own way.

1083
01:35:18,240 --> 01:35:19,240
Our own way.

1084
01:36:15,800 --> 01:36:19,600
Çiçek, you look beautiful.

1085
01:36:20,760 --> 01:36:23,120
I dressed according to the
meaning and importance of today.

1086
01:36:23,360 --> 01:36:24,360
What do you mean?

1087
01:36:25,200 --> 01:36:26,680
We’re going out together.

1088
01:36:29,000 --> 01:36:32,320
You look so beautiful.

1089
01:36:32,720 --> 01:36:33,880
You’re glowing like the moon.

1090
01:36:34,560 --> 01:36:37,560
I look so plain next to you, my love.

1091
01:36:38,480 --> 01:36:40,520
It’s fine, you’re handsome in every way.

1092
01:36:41,040 --> 01:36:45,120
But I thought you’d
wear a suit or something.

1093
01:36:45,800 --> 01:36:46,880
A suit?

1094
01:36:48,280 --> 01:36:50,120
Anyway, forget it.

1095
01:36:51,880 --> 01:36:53,040
So? Where are we going now?

1096
01:36:55,080 --> 01:36:58,880
I was thinking we’d go to a
tea garden and have some tea.

1097
01:37:01,320 --> 01:37:02,320
A tea garden?

1098
01:37:04,120 --> 01:37:07,880
Was today a special
day and I missed it hun?

1099
01:37:09,720 --> 01:37:10,720
I don’t know.

1100
01:37:11,920 --> 01:37:13,640
I think you should answer that.

1101
01:37:15,240 --> 01:37:17,040
Maybe it’s not a special moment yet.

1102
01:37:17,840 --> 01:37:20,120
But that doesn’t mean it
won’t be special from now on.

1103
01:37:20,400 --> 01:37:21,400
Right?

1104
01:37:21,800 --> 01:37:25,239
For me, every day I spend with you,

1105
01:37:25,240 --> 01:37:29,640
every minute, every hour,
every second is special, Çiçek.

1106
01:37:38,800 --> 01:37:39,800
I can’t believe this.

1107
01:37:40,280 --> 01:37:41,920
Are you going to do this here, right now?

1108
01:37:43,840 --> 01:37:45,920
Wait, before you ask, let me answer.

1109
01:37:46,520 --> 01:37:47,520
Yes, yes, yes.

1110
01:37:49,640 --> 01:37:51,640
Yes to what, Çiçek?

1111
01:37:51,760 --> 01:37:53,120
My shoelace came undone.

1112
01:37:53,680 --> 01:37:55,480
I was going to tie it so we could head out.

1113
01:38:02,280 --> 01:38:03,280
Let’s go.

1114
01:38:05,680 --> 01:38:07,640
Why did you call me here?

1115
01:38:08,840 --> 01:38:11,359
So we could talk, Çiçek, what happened?

1116
01:38:11,360 --> 01:38:13,040
What are we going to talk about?

1117
01:38:13,480 --> 01:38:15,200
I have a lot of work there, alright?

1118
01:38:15,600 --> 01:38:16,800
What happened now, Çiçek?

1119
01:38:17,000 --> 01:38:18,280
I’m leaving.

1120
01:38:19,280 --> 01:38:20,720
-Çiçek, Çiçek... -Shut up!

1121
01:38:26,880 --> 01:38:28,240
Çiçek?

1122
01:38:29,280 --> 01:38:30,280
Good grief.

1123
01:38:32,120 --> 01:38:33,640
What did I do now?

1124
01:38:54,720 --> 01:38:55,920
I said you’re leaving here.

1125
01:38:56,960 --> 01:38:57,960
Leaving where?

1126
01:38:58,400 --> 01:38:59,520
What are you talking about?

1127
01:38:59,880 --> 01:39:00,880
Have you lost your mind?

1128
01:39:02,920 --> 01:39:03,920
I have.

1129
01:39:04,760 --> 01:39:05,760
Everything is arranged.

1130
01:39:07,640 --> 01:39:09,880
You’ll stay in London until
the divorce period is over.

1131
01:39:11,080 --> 01:39:14,080
Your plane ticket and all the information
you need are inside the envelope.

1132
01:39:58,240 --> 01:40:00,320
You’ve thrown yourself
into work again at this hour?

1133
01:40:05,040 --> 01:40:07,760
I mean to, but I haven’t managed yet.

1134
01:40:10,080 --> 01:40:11,480
Is there anything I can do?

1135
01:40:12,600 --> 01:40:13,600
No, thanks.

1136
01:40:14,560 --> 01:40:16,680
Alright then, I’ll take off.

1137
01:40:22,040 --> 01:40:23,040
By the way...

1138
01:40:25,680 --> 01:40:27,960
If you don’t want to, you should say it.

1139
01:40:29,000 --> 01:40:30,000
Say what?

1140
01:40:30,160 --> 01:40:31,160
What else?

1141
01:40:31,800 --> 01:40:33,000
That you don’t want her to go.

1142
01:40:34,560 --> 01:40:37,920
Wait, let me finish first, then
you talk. One at a time, alright?

1143
01:40:41,840 --> 01:40:43,560
It’s obvious Mercan doesn’t want to go.

1144
01:40:43,840 --> 01:40:46,280
And looking at you, you don’t
really want to send her either.

1145
01:40:48,520 --> 01:40:50,440
Then do something before you regret it.

1146
01:40:51,080 --> 01:40:52,800
Say don’t go. Say I changed my mind.

1147
01:40:54,280 --> 01:40:56,400
Isn’t it better to say it
than to bottle it up, Ateş?

1148
01:41:02,480 --> 01:41:04,640
Anyway, I won’t push it any further.

1149
01:41:14,480 --> 01:41:16,080
It’s obvious Mercan doesn’t want to go.

1150
01:41:16,440 --> 01:41:18,880
And looking at you, you don’t
really want to send her either.

1151
01:41:19,040 --> 01:41:20,640
Then do something before you regret it.

1152
01:41:21,200 --> 01:41:23,480
Say don’t go. Say I changed my mind.

1153
01:41:24,480 --> 01:41:26,600
Isn’t it better to say it
than to bottle it up, Ateş?

1154
01:42:38,480 --> 01:42:39,480
Hello.

1155
01:42:41,520 --> 01:42:42,640
Yes, Mr. Emrah.

1156
01:42:47,000 --> 01:42:48,000
Today?

1157
01:42:50,920 --> 01:42:52,880
Alright, we’ll try to handle it.

1158
01:42:53,760 --> 01:42:55,200
What time is it in the US right now?

1159
01:42:58,440 --> 01:43:00,880
I hope we can make it
before your workday ends.

1160
01:43:02,440 --> 01:43:03,440
Alright.

1161
01:43:14,640 --> 01:43:15,960
Where are you at this hour?

1162
01:44:22,080 --> 01:44:24,440
Why are you still here?

1163
01:44:28,680 --> 01:44:30,840
You didn’t want to see my face anyway.

1164
01:44:34,960 --> 01:44:35,960
Tonight’s like this.

1165
01:44:38,560 --> 01:44:39,560
I have some work to do.

1166
01:44:40,760 --> 01:44:41,760
You enjoy yourself.

1167
01:44:48,040 --> 01:44:49,400
I saw your face again anyway.

1168
01:44:50,920 --> 01:44:51,920
I couldn’t get away.

1169
01:44:56,920 --> 01:44:59,560
What enjoyment are you talking about?

1170
01:45:00,240 --> 01:45:01,320
Mr. Emrah called.

1171
01:45:02,400 --> 01:45:04,760
He wants the final version of
the project in the US, today.

1172
01:45:07,720 --> 01:45:11,200
I said we’d handle it, but
I’m not sure we can make it.

1173
01:45:14,160 --> 01:45:16,080
Doesn’t this man know
about the time difference?

1174
01:45:20,240 --> 01:45:21,240
Anyway.

1175
01:45:22,600 --> 01:45:23,600
Come on, sit down.

1176
01:45:23,640 --> 01:45:24,920
Let’s start as soon as possible.

1177
01:47:45,680 --> 01:47:47,760
She’s so natural.

1178
01:47:48,360 --> 01:47:50,000
She isn’t even aware of her beauty.

1179
01:47:56,800 --> 01:47:58,400
She’s not aware of anything.

1180
01:47:59,320 --> 01:48:02,040
Even this silence right now is so precious.

1181
01:48:03,160 --> 01:48:06,600
I’m afraid if I speak,
I’ll break the spell.

1182
01:48:29,920 --> 01:48:31,000
I wish you’d tell me.

1183
01:48:32,040 --> 01:48:34,080
I wish I could read your mind.

1184
01:48:37,720 --> 01:48:39,520
I’m only a few steps away.

1185
01:48:41,040 --> 01:48:42,880
But between us there’s an impossible...

1186
01:48:43,000 --> 01:48:44,520
glass wall, as if.

1187
01:50:48,400 --> 01:50:50,120
It just won’t close.

1188
01:50:54,720 --> 01:50:55,720
I’ll get it.

1189
01:51:08,160 --> 01:51:09,160
Are you okay?

1190
01:51:10,000 --> 01:51:11,000
Did it hurt?

1191
01:51:13,360 --> 01:51:14,360
A little.

1192
01:51:15,720 --> 01:51:16,800
Did yours hurt?

1193
01:51:23,760 --> 01:51:24,760
A little.

1194
01:51:26,520 --> 01:51:27,800
Are you alright then?

1195
01:51:29,080 --> 01:51:30,080
I didn’t die.

1196
01:51:30,520 --> 01:51:31,520
You?

1197
01:51:33,000 --> 01:51:33,600
Should I get some ice?

1198
01:51:33,920 --> 01:51:34,920
No need.

1199
01:51:36,880 --> 01:51:39,040
It hurt, but I didn’t die either.

1200
01:51:39,200 --> 01:51:40,200
My head’s solid.

1201
01:51:42,320 --> 01:51:45,080
I figured that much.

1202
01:51:49,360 --> 01:51:50,640
This still hasn’t closed either.

1203
01:52:18,800 --> 01:52:20,040
Try to be a bit careful.

1204
01:52:21,640 --> 01:52:22,640
Because of you.

1205
01:52:23,160 --> 01:52:25,096
Your clumsiness kicked in
again first thing in the morning.

1206
01:52:25,120 --> 01:52:26,600
Everything is my fault anyway.

1207
01:52:30,480 --> 01:52:31,480
Get out of here.

1208
01:53:01,560 --> 01:53:02,560
You didn’t say anything.

1209
01:53:04,800 --> 01:53:06,680
What can I say?

1210
01:53:17,000 --> 01:53:18,000
Yes or no.

1211
01:53:21,440 --> 01:53:27,040
I mean, my home, my job, my family,
my friends, everything is here.

1212
01:53:28,600 --> 01:53:29,600
I’m thinking.

1213
01:53:30,680 --> 01:53:31,680
Why are you thinking?

1214
01:53:33,120 --> 01:53:34,440
Why are you asking all this?

1215
01:53:37,680 --> 01:53:39,760
I’m asking because you’re
not answering my question.

1216
01:53:42,640 --> 01:53:45,320
Is it that easy to just
drop everything and leave?

1217
01:53:47,200 --> 01:53:48,240
I didn’t say it was easy.

1218
01:53:49,480 --> 01:53:51,120
And you know it’s not easy.

1219
01:53:53,360 --> 01:53:56,360
Knowing that and still trying to send
me away isn’t worse, don’t you think?

1220
01:53:56,760 --> 01:53:58,000
I’m not a child.

1221
01:53:58,240 --> 01:53:59,680
My life isn’t a child’s game either.

1222
01:54:01,160 --> 01:54:03,920
Why should I go when you say
go, or stay when you say stay?

1223
01:54:07,240 --> 01:54:08,240
So?

1224
01:54:13,120 --> 01:54:14,280
So what?

1225
01:54:18,320 --> 01:54:19,320
So that’s it.

1226
01:54:27,040 --> 01:54:28,560
I’m going to go change.

1227
01:54:45,520 --> 01:54:47,120
It’s obvious Mercan doesn’t want to go.

1228
01:54:47,400 --> 01:54:49,560
And looking at you, you
don’t want to send her either.

1229
01:54:49,800 --> 01:54:51,920
Isn’t it better to say it
than to bottle it up, Ateş?

1230
01:55:01,960 --> 01:55:02,760
I did it.

1231
01:55:02,920 --> 01:55:03,920
Did you like it?

1232
01:55:04,720 --> 01:55:05,680
Zehra, well done.

1233
01:55:05,720 --> 01:55:06,720
It looks great.

1234
01:55:08,240 --> 01:55:09,240
Enjoy it.

1235
01:55:17,720 --> 01:55:18,720
Hey.

1236
01:55:19,200 --> 01:55:20,760
What do you think you’re doing?

1237
01:55:21,160 --> 01:55:22,160
Hands off.

1238
01:55:22,840 --> 01:55:25,320
I just wanted to hold your
hand, Zehra, I didn’t do anything.

1239
01:55:25,760 --> 01:55:26,760
No.

1240
01:55:27,600 --> 01:55:28,600
Why not?

1241
01:55:29,360 --> 01:55:31,440
I’m not like the girls
you think I am, alright?

1242
01:55:33,640 --> 01:55:35,280
I don’t have any girls like that in mind.

1243
01:55:36,320 --> 01:55:37,600
I don’t know about that anymore.

1244
01:55:41,640 --> 01:55:42,880
I swear I don’t, Zehra.

1245
01:55:51,000 --> 01:55:52,000
I said no.

1246
01:55:53,600 --> 01:55:55,480
What if someone sees us?

1247
01:55:55,880 --> 01:55:57,000
So what if they do?

1248
01:55:57,040 --> 01:55:58,040
What happens then?

1249
01:55:58,080 --> 01:55:59,280
What do you mean what happens?

1250
01:55:59,800 --> 01:56:01,080
What will they think about me?

1251
01:56:02,680 --> 01:56:04,000
What would they think, Zehra?

1252
01:56:04,120 --> 01:56:05,640
There’s nothing bad about this.

1253
01:56:14,240 --> 01:56:15,240
I...

1254
01:56:15,760 --> 01:56:17,200
I really like you, Zehra.

1255
01:56:19,520 --> 01:56:20,640
You know that too.

1256
01:56:25,960 --> 01:56:27,560
I don’t know anything like that.

1257
01:56:29,280 --> 01:56:30,720
Time will tell anyway.

1258
01:56:31,560 --> 01:56:32,760
You can’t trust men.

1259
01:56:34,280 --> 01:56:35,280
Hold on a second.

1260
01:56:35,760 --> 01:56:37,560
I’m not one of the men
you think I am either.

1261
01:56:38,000 --> 01:56:39,360
I don’t let go of the hand I hold.

1262
01:56:40,520 --> 01:56:41,680
When I love, I love for real.

1263
01:56:43,680 --> 01:56:44,720
I love like a man should.

1264
01:56:48,360 --> 01:56:49,720
Anyway, I have to go.

1265
01:56:51,880 --> 01:56:52,880
Wait a second.

1266
01:56:58,400 --> 01:57:00,280
Well done.

1267
01:57:01,480 --> 01:57:02,480
Enjoy it.

1268
01:57:20,320 --> 01:57:22,640
You really did make this beautifully.

1269
01:57:28,800 --> 01:57:29,800
Take a look at this.

1270
01:57:30,160 --> 01:57:30,480
Yeah.

1271
01:57:30,760 --> 01:57:33,000
Hold on for God’s sake, I
want to ask you something.

1272
01:57:33,960 --> 01:57:35,240
Was the concert good last night?

1273
01:57:35,600 --> 01:57:36,600
More than good.

1274
01:57:37,240 --> 01:57:38,960
I haven’t had that much fun in a long time.

1275
01:57:40,240 --> 01:57:42,840
And I think I had a part in that.

1276
01:57:43,480 --> 01:57:44,480
Of course.

1277
01:57:44,600 --> 01:57:46,559
Thanks to you, it was a lovely evening.

1278
01:57:46,560 --> 01:57:48,400
So would we go again?

1279
01:57:48,880 --> 01:57:49,880
Why not?

1280
01:57:53,160 --> 01:57:56,800
Then will you let me buy you
a coffee on the terrace now?

1281
01:57:57,480 --> 01:57:58,480
Alright. Come on then.

1282
01:57:58,640 --> 01:57:59,640
Let’s go.

1283
01:58:00,080 --> 01:58:01,480
It was pretty productive, honestly.

1284
01:58:05,280 --> 01:58:06,760
I know these things.

1285
01:58:08,480 --> 01:58:09,640
I know these things.

1286
01:58:09,760 --> 01:58:10,840
I’m a man of love, love.

1287
01:58:11,680 --> 01:58:12,680
I told you.

1288
01:58:18,480 --> 01:58:19,800
I yawned, honestly.

1289
01:58:20,920 --> 01:58:22,360
You jinxed me in two minutes.

1290
01:58:35,160 --> 01:58:36,920
Were you very tired last night?

1291
01:58:37,360 --> 01:58:39,200
When you’re on your
feet all night, of course.

1292
01:58:40,080 --> 01:58:41,280
No, Mr. Nezir.

1293
01:58:42,160 --> 01:58:44,320
Actually, I went to bed early last night.

1294
01:58:44,440 --> 01:58:45,600
I slept like a baby.

1295
01:58:53,320 --> 01:58:54,760
That’s what Mr. Nezir says.

1296
01:58:55,400 --> 01:58:55,800
You know, at the...

1297
01:58:55,880 --> 01:58:56,880
He slept at the concert.

1298
01:59:02,040 --> 01:59:04,280
Must be old age, right?

1299
01:59:11,000 --> 01:59:13,360
Nothing slips past you, does it?

1300
01:59:18,760 --> 01:59:20,240
I didn’t sleep, sweetheart.

1301
01:59:20,360 --> 01:59:22,040
I just dozed off a little, like this.

1302
01:59:22,840 --> 01:59:26,000
But this old age thing and all...

1303
01:59:30,320 --> 01:59:31,320
What was I saying?

1304
01:59:31,440 --> 01:59:33,200
You go make yourself
a black turkish coffee.

1305
01:59:34,720 --> 01:59:35,920
Or take a vitamin.

1306
01:59:36,520 --> 01:59:38,360
Coffee will give you palpitations now.

1307
01:59:44,400 --> 01:59:46,320
You were about to ruin the whole thing.

1308
01:59:47,080 --> 01:59:48,080
I really was.

1309
01:59:50,160 --> 01:59:51,600
But you saved it well.

1310
01:59:52,840 --> 01:59:55,160
You stepped in at just
the right time, bravo.

1311
01:59:56,640 --> 01:59:59,360
Let’s tell Burak to
treat us to a meal for this.

1312
01:59:59,920 --> 02:00:00,520
Oh come on.

1313
02:00:00,600 --> 02:00:01,600
Seriously, enough.

1314
02:00:04,760 --> 02:00:07,920
But let me tell you, this
old age talk was out of line.

1315
02:00:09,440 --> 02:00:11,800
Ay Yaşar, I won’t put
up with you, you know that?

1316
02:00:14,840 --> 02:00:16,280
Good grief.

1317
02:00:40,520 --> 02:00:41,640
Will you get out of my way?

1318
02:00:42,600 --> 02:00:43,600
I’m not moving.

1319
02:00:44,080 --> 02:00:45,080
What are you going to do?

1320
02:00:46,200 --> 02:00:46,960
What’s your problem?

1321
02:00:47,160 --> 02:00:48,160
What do you want?

1322
02:00:50,160 --> 02:00:51,160
For you to disappear.

1323
02:00:51,680 --> 02:00:52,800
Forever, actually.

1324
02:00:54,040 --> 02:00:55,720
That much is obvious.

1325
02:00:56,840 --> 02:00:57,840
But why?

1326
02:00:59,120 --> 02:01:01,440
Because I hate you.

1327
02:01:03,480 --> 02:01:04,480
Why do you hate me?

1328
02:01:05,240 --> 02:01:07,080
We don’t even really know each other.

1329
02:01:07,800 --> 02:01:09,360
What I know is more than enough for me.

1330
02:01:10,120 --> 02:01:11,320
Look, I’m honestly asking.

1331
02:01:11,520 --> 02:01:13,040
Because I honestly don’t understand.

1332
02:01:14,720 --> 02:01:16,480
Why all this anger, this hatred?

1333
02:01:18,800 --> 02:01:21,000
Don’t tire yourself trying to understand.

1334
02:01:21,920 --> 02:01:24,160
I don’t need a reason for it.

1335
02:01:26,560 --> 02:01:28,160
Your existence is enough.

1336
02:01:29,880 --> 02:01:34,320
In fact, there’s no one in
this world I hate more than you.

1337
02:01:36,000 --> 02:01:40,640
I’ll find a way and poison
every single day of yours.

1338
02:01:42,160 --> 02:01:43,880
I’ll never give you peace.

1339
02:01:47,080 --> 02:01:49,360
I won’t listen to this
insane nonsense anymore.

1340
02:01:50,480 --> 02:01:52,720
If I were you, I’d take it seriously.

1341
02:01:52,840 --> 02:01:55,080
-Or else... -Or else what?

1342
02:01:55,520 --> 02:01:56,720
What would you do?

1343
02:01:57,240 --> 02:01:58,240
Say it.

1344
02:01:58,480 --> 02:01:58,920
What would you do?

1345
02:01:59,080 --> 02:02:00,080
Go on, say it.

1346
02:02:02,120 --> 02:02:03,120
What was the problem?

1347
02:02:04,680 --> 02:02:06,200
She insulted me.

1348
02:02:07,760 --> 02:02:10,080
Calling me crazy wasn’t
enough, she even threatened me.

1349
02:02:11,320 --> 02:02:12,560
Did I threaten you?

1350
02:02:13,440 --> 02:02:14,600
This is unbelievable.

1351
02:02:17,680 --> 02:02:20,960
I won’t even get into a war of words
with you and sink to your level, alright?

1352
02:02:21,240 --> 02:02:23,280
For you to get to my level...

1353
02:02:23,440 --> 02:02:24,560
Aslı, enough.

1354
02:02:26,280 --> 02:02:28,120
Don’t drag it out,
whatever it is, end it now.

1355
02:02:29,720 --> 02:02:32,440
I’m the one being threatened, and
I’m still the one getting scolded.

1356
02:02:34,240 --> 02:02:36,120
Patience, she’s still saying threatened.

1357
02:02:37,080 --> 02:02:38,720
She has serious issues, just so you know.

1358
02:02:41,040 --> 02:02:41,520
Aslı, stop.

1359
02:02:42,040 --> 02:02:43,040
What are you doing?

1360
02:02:44,000 --> 02:02:45,880
Why are you always mad at me?

1361
02:02:46,560 --> 02:02:48,480
Will you say a word to her too, I wonder?

1362
02:02:48,720 --> 02:02:49,720
Enough already.

1363
02:02:50,560 --> 02:02:51,880
What is this?

1364
02:02:52,040 --> 02:02:53,040
Like a child.

1365
02:02:54,560 --> 02:02:55,720
Stop dealing with her.

1366
02:03:09,160 --> 02:03:11,600
I’ll make your life worse
than death, you little snake.

1367
02:03:13,560 --> 02:03:16,240
You’ll beg to die...

1368
02:03:17,000 --> 02:03:19,240
but your wish won’t come true right away.

1369
02:03:21,520 --> 02:03:23,480
I’ll enjoy watching you writhe in pain.

1370
02:03:59,800 --> 02:04:01,200
I was looking for you too, my girl.

1371
02:04:01,960 --> 02:04:02,960
Why? What happened?

1372
02:04:03,400 --> 02:04:04,560
Nothing happened, dear.

1373
02:04:05,400 --> 02:04:07,800
I thought we could go shopping together.

1374
02:04:08,240 --> 02:04:10,360
I’ll get myself a nice evening dress.

1375
02:04:13,880 --> 02:04:15,520
You’ll get some warm clothes too.

1376
02:04:16,320 --> 02:04:17,960
London gets cold this season.

1377
02:04:19,320 --> 02:04:20,680
I haven’t decided yet, mom.

1378
02:04:21,080 --> 02:04:22,080
I’m thinking.

1379
02:04:23,080 --> 02:04:24,400
What is there to think about?

1380
02:04:24,440 --> 02:04:25,480
What do you mean what?

1381
02:04:26,800 --> 02:04:28,839
Mom, a life I don’t want is
being forced on me constantly.

1382
02:04:28,840 --> 02:04:29,840
Are you aware of that?

1383
02:04:31,720 --> 02:04:34,120
Alright, my girl, but is there another way?

1384
02:04:35,720 --> 02:04:37,040
The right thing is for you to go.

1385
02:04:38,520 --> 02:04:42,560
Both for you and for us.

1386
02:04:43,680 --> 02:04:45,760
There’s been nothing
good for me for a long time.

1387
02:04:47,640 --> 02:04:50,320
Mercan my girl, I’m very upset too.

1388
02:04:52,200 --> 02:04:53,800
But there’s nothing you can do.

1389
02:04:55,000 --> 02:04:58,320
I want to get rid of these
people as soon as possible as well.

1390
02:05:03,480 --> 02:05:05,400
You wouldn’t risk
everything we have, would you?

1391
02:05:08,360 --> 02:05:10,360
Don’t pretend you’re thinking of me, mom.

1392
02:05:11,200 --> 02:05:13,400
I know what you and dad
are really worried about.

1393
02:06:38,120 --> 02:06:39,720
If you don’t want it, you should say it.

1394
02:06:40,200 --> 02:06:40,520
Say what?

1395
02:06:41,080 --> 02:06:42,080
What else?

1396
02:06:42,400 --> 02:06:43,600
That you don’t want her to go.

1397
02:07:04,760 --> 02:07:06,480
Should I say don’t go?

1398
02:07:10,440 --> 02:07:11,440
If I say it...

1399
02:07:13,800 --> 02:07:15,080
She doesn’t want to go anyway.

1400
02:07:20,400 --> 02:07:22,200
But this means staying
married to me forever.

1401
02:07:47,560 --> 02:07:48,720
I was coming to you too.

1402
02:07:49,800 --> 02:07:50,120
To you...

1403
02:07:50,121 --> 02:07:52,480
You were probably going to
ask what decision I’d make.

1404
02:08:02,080 --> 02:08:03,600
That’s what I came to tell you.

1405
02:08:07,600 --> 02:08:09,160
If you say don’t go.

1406
02:08:10,120 --> 02:08:11,120
If you stay.

1407
02:08:19,920 --> 02:08:21,480
Since you want it this much.

1408
02:08:26,360 --> 02:08:27,360
Alright.

1409
02:08:40,880 --> 02:08:42,080
I accept your offer.

1410
02:08:46,720 --> 02:08:47,720
Don’t go.

1411
02:08:53,120 --> 02:08:54,200
I’m going to London.

1412
02:11:08,280 --> 02:11:09,280
Let me help.

1413
02:11:16,480 --> 02:11:17,480
I don't want it.

1414
02:12:02,800 --> 02:12:04,160
Give me your hand.

1415
02:12:13,080 --> 02:12:14,600
-Let go! -Stay still.

1416
02:12:15,440 --> 02:12:17,200
-I said, let go! -I said stay still!

1417
02:12:37,640 --> 02:12:40,240
Keep resisting. I’ll fight
you for hours if I have to.

1418
02:12:40,400 --> 02:12:41,960
No problem.

1419
02:13:08,720 --> 02:13:10,520
Your stubbornness won’t work on me.

1420
02:13:15,600 --> 02:13:16,880
Take it off all you want.

1421
02:13:18,600 --> 02:13:20,680
You’ll have to put it back every time.

1422
02:13:24,680 --> 02:13:26,200
This fight will last forever.

1423
02:13:32,960 --> 02:13:34,960
I said you were no different from Nezir.

1424
02:13:35,840 --> 02:13:36,880
I was wrong.

1425
02:13:38,200 --> 02:13:39,760
You’re worse.

1426
02:14:12,080 --> 02:14:13,440
You haven’t seen anything yet.

1427
02:14:16,480 --> 02:14:17,640
I’m just getting started.

1428
02:16:22,280 --> 02:16:23,480
Hold on tight.

1429
02:17:16,680 --> 02:17:17,760
What do you want?

1430
02:17:22,320 --> 02:17:24,000
Aren't you done with your torture?

1431
02:17:48,880 --> 02:17:49,880
Not yet.

1432
02:17:56,080 --> 02:17:57,320
It's going to be a long night.

1433
02:18:03,040 --> 02:18:04,520
Let's make something clear.

1434
02:18:10,200 --> 02:18:11,800
You can't come in without permission.

1435
02:18:19,280 --> 02:18:20,600
I don't take permission.

1436
02:18:25,240 --> 02:18:26,400
I give it.

1437
02:18:32,800 --> 02:18:33,840
If i want to.

1438
02:18:43,560 --> 02:18:44,560
You ran.

1439
02:18:49,520 --> 02:18:51,720
But you came back on your own.

1440
02:18:57,960 --> 02:19:00,160
It means you accepted everything.

1441
02:19:09,680 --> 02:19:11,440
What… What do you mean "everything"?

1442
02:19:13,880 --> 02:19:14,880
Everything.

1443
02:19:18,560 --> 02:19:20,040
What do you mean by that?

1444
02:19:20,920 --> 02:19:22,200
I don't understand.

1445
02:20:11,800 --> 02:20:12,800
Shame.

1446
02:20:25,440 --> 02:20:26,840
Seriously?

1447
02:20:33,800 --> 02:20:34,800
Insolent.

1448
02:20:40,600 --> 02:20:42,200
If you'll excuse me.

1449
02:21:12,240 --> 02:21:13,960
God, help me.

1450
02:21:58,240 --> 02:22:00,640
You won' ever let me get a
moment of peace, will you?

1451
02:22:01,680 --> 02:22:03,280
So that you can't cause problems for me.

1452
02:22:07,000 --> 02:22:08,360
It's not that I worry about you.

1453
02:22:09,280 --> 02:22:10,760
In case you hurt yourself.

1454
02:22:11,240 --> 02:22:12,240
I can't be bothered.
